 ## [Unreleased]
 
-(empty)
+### 1.11.9 - Web UI audit + graceful backend-drift handling (2026-04)
+
+### Added
+- **(ui-audit) puppeteer-driven UI audit script.** `scripts/ui-audit.js`
+  launches headless Chromium (bundled by `puppeteer`) and walks every C4
+  view by priming `localStorage` (`c4.authToken`, `c4.topView`,
+  `c4.sidebar.mode`, `c4.detail.mode`) on a root load, reloading, and
+  clicking the first worker row for the three detail variants. Per view
+  it captures console errors/warnings (vite + SSE-nav-timeout noise
+  filtered), `pageerror` uncaught throws, `requestfailed` + 4xx response
+  entries (same-origin only, source-map / `@vite/client` ignored), and a
+  layout probe that walks ancestor computed styles before flagging
+  zero-size `<svg>` or missing-icon elements (so tailwind `md:hidden`
+  sidebar glyphs stop showing up as bugs). A sibling
+  `scripts/ui-audit-login.js` reads the silofox password from
+  `/tmp/c4-silofox-cred` via `fs.readFileSync`, posts to
+  `/api/auth/login`, and writes the JWT to `/tmp/c4-audit-token.json`
+  (mode 600) so the password never lands on argv / shell history. Audit
+  output is `scripts/ui-audit-report.json` (git-ignored).
+- **(ui-audit) environment-drift classification.** Before the view loop,
+  the audit probes `/api/resize`, `/api/workflows`, and
+  `/api/slack/events` against the live daemon. If those return 404 or
+  the 200 SPA-HTML fallback, the URLs land in
+  `report.staleDaemonRoutes` and subsequent 404s on those routes are
+  counted under `summary.environment` instead of `summary.critical`, so
+  the iterative audit is not gated on a daemon restart that would kill
+  the worker running the audit.
+
+### Changed
+- **(web) `apiGet` / `apiPost` guard against static-server HTML
+  fallbacks.** `web/src/lib/api.ts` now routes every read through a
+  private `readJson<T>(res, url)` helper that requires
+  `content-type: application/json` before calling `res.json()`. When
+  the daemon is missing a route and the static fallback replies
+  `200 index.html`, callers see
+  `Expected JSON from /api/workflows but got text/html; charset=utf-8`
+  instead of the opaque
+  `Unexpected token '<', "<!doctype "... is not valid JSON`
+  that `WorkflowEditor` was pushing into its `role="alert"` surface.
+- **(web) `WorkerDetail` resize degrades gracefully against older
+  daemons.** `web/src/components/WorkerDetail.tsx` adds
+  `resizeUnsupportedRef`: the first 404 from `POST /api/resize` (daemon
+  predates the 8.13 route) flips the flag, the callback short-circuits
+  on entry, and the auto-fit + manual-cols effects stop re-posting.
+  Previously each window resize or font-size change re-hit the 404 and
+  stamped `resize failed: HTTP 404` into `actionMsg`, so users on
+  older daemons saw a permanent error pill.
+- **(dev) `package.json` gains `puppeteer` as a `devDependency`.** The
+  bundled Chromium needs `libatk1.0-0`, `libatk-bridge2.0-0`, `libcups2`,
+  `libxcomposite1`, `libxdamage1`, `libatspi2.0-0` on Ubuntu — see
+  `patches/1.11.9-ui-audit.md` for the one-shot apt line. `.gitignore`
+  updated so the generated report JSON is not committed.
 
