index 0000000..0c063b5
--- /dev/null
+++ b/patches/1.11.9-ui-audit.md
@@ -0,0 +1,158 @@
+# 1.11.9 - Web UI audit + graceful backend-drift handling (2026-04)
+
+## Goal
+
+Stand up an autonomous UI audit for the C4 web console and land the
+web-side fixes the audit surfaces. The audit must (a) be runnable from
+inside a c4 worker without touching the running daemon/vite (restarting
+either would kill the worker doing the audit), and (b) never hold
+credentials on argv.
+
+Addresses TODO 8.17.
+
+## What lands
+
+### Audit tooling
+
+- `scripts/ui-audit-login.js` — reads the silofox password from
+  `/tmp/c4-silofox-cred` via `fs.readFileSync`, posts
+  `/api/auth/login`, and writes the JWT to
+  `/tmp/c4-audit-token.json` (mode 600). The password never shows
+  up on argv or in shell history. The downstream audit script only
+  reads the token file, never the credential file.
+- `scripts/ui-audit.js` — puppeteer-driven headless Chromium. Walks
+  every user-facing view of the console:
+  - `login` (unauthenticated)
+  - `worker-list` (`topView=workers, sidebarMode=list`)
+  - `hierarchy-tree` (`topView=workers, sidebarMode=tree`)
+  - `worker-detail-terminal` / `worker-detail-chat` /
+    `worker-detail-control` (after clicking the first worker row)
+  - `history` / `chat` / `workflows` (`topView` switches)
+
+  Each view runs through the same pipeline: load root, prime
+  `localStorage` (`c4.authToken` + the per-view keys), reload with
+  `waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded'` (an SSE `EventSource` keeps
+  `networkidle0` from ever settling), sleep 1.5s, run an optional
+  `postLoad` click, 600ms settle, probe.
+
+  Collectors:
+  - `page.on('console', ...)` — keep only `error` + `warning`;
+    filter `[vite]` HMR chatter, `Download the React DevTools`,
+    and the audit-internal `nav fallback:` notice.
+  - `page.on('pageerror', ...)` — uncaught throws + rejections.
+  - `page.on('response', ...)` — same-origin 4xx+, skipping
+    `.map`, `/.well-known/`, `@vite/client`, `@react-refresh`,
+    `__open-in-editor`.
+  - `page.on('requestfailed', ...)` — transport / DNS / abort.
+  - In-page layout probe — zero-size visible images, zero-size or
+    empty `<svg>`, `role="alert"` surfaced text. Visibility is
+    decided by walking ancestors' computed styles so Tailwind's
+    `md:hidden` responsive utilities do not masquerade as zero-size
+    bugs.
+
+  Output: `scripts/ui-audit-report.json` (git-ignored). Summary has
+  four buckets:
+  - `critical` — page errors, console.error, same-origin 4xx,
+    visible red alerts, broken lucide.
+  - `warning` — console.warning, zero-size imgs/svgs, empty svgs,
+    viewport overflow.
+  - `info` — neutral role=alert surfaces.
+  - `environment` — 4xx responses on routes that the running
+    daemon is missing (probed once at audit start against the
+    known post-main routes `/api/resize`, `/api/workflows`,
+    `/api/slack/events`). These are held out of `critical` so the
+    audit loop is not gated on a daemon restart — restarting the
+    daemon from inside a worker kills the worker.
+
+### Web fixes surfaced by the audit
+
+1. **`web/src/lib/api.ts` now guards against HTML-as-JSON fallback
+   bodies.** Both `apiGet` and `apiPost` go through a private
+   `readJson<T>(res, url)` that short-circuits when
+   `content-type` is missing `application/json` and throws
+   `Expected JSON from <url> but got <content-type>`. Previously
+   the daemon's static-server fallback (unknown non-/api GET → 200
+   `index.html`) caused `res.json()` to throw the opaque
+   `Unexpected token '<', "<!doctype "... is not valid JSON`
+   which the `WorkflowEditor` surfaced to users as-is through its
+   `role="alert"` surface.
+
+2. **`web/src/components/WorkerDetail.tsx` stops retrying resize
+   against older daemons.** Added `resizeUnsupportedRef`. On the
+   first `404` from `POST /api/resize` (daemon predates the 8.13
+   `/resize` route) the flag flips, `requestResize` short-circuits
+   on entry, and the auto-fit / manual-cols effects stop posting
+   further attempts. Previously every window resize or font-size
+   bump re-hit the 404 and stamped
+   `resize failed: HTTP 404` into `actionMsg`, so users on older
+   daemons saw a permanent red pill.
+
+Both fixes are defensive. On a fully-deployed stack they are
+no-ops because the endpoints reply 200 + JSON.
+
+### Dev-deps + runtime
+
+- `package.json` picks up `puppeteer` as a devDependency
+  (bundled Chromium, no system browser required).
+- `package-lock.json` regenerates accordingly.
+- `.gitignore` now excludes `scripts/ui-audit-report.json`.
+
+## One-time system deps (Ubuntu)
+
+Puppeteer's bundled Chromium needs the following apt packages. Run once
+per machine:
+
+```bash
+apt-get install -y libatk1.0-0 libatk-bridge2.0-0 libcups2 \
+  libxcomposite1 libxdamage1 libatspi2.0-0
+```
+
+(Single command; no compound chain. All transitive deps come in via
+standard apt resolution.)
+
+## How to run
+
+```bash
+node scripts/ui-audit-login.js            # writes /tmp/c4-audit-token.json
+node scripts/ui-audit.js                  # writes scripts/ui-audit-report.json
+```
+
+Override the target with `C4_AUDIT_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5174` when
+the daemon or a second vite instance is on a different port. Override
+the token path with `C4_AUDIT_TOKEN_FILE=...` and the credential path
+with `C4_CRED_FILE=...`.
+
+## Verification
+
+Audit against a worktree-served vite (`npm --prefix web run dev --
+--host 127.0.0.1 --port 5174`) + the same running daemon:
+
+```
+[audit] note: running daemon is missing these routes (treated as
+  environment drift, not UI bugs):
+  /api/resize, /api/workflows, /api/slack/events
+[audit] totals: critical=0 warning=0 info=1 environment=2
+```
+
+The single info alert is the `WorkflowEditor` correctly surfacing the
+new, readable env-drift message (`Expected JSON from /api/workflows
+but got text/html; charset=utf-8`). The two environment entries are the
+unavoidable first probes to the pre-8.13 daemon — after each first 404,
+`resizeUnsupportedRef` prevents further attempts and the UI stays
+quiet.
+
+`npm --prefix web run build` (tsc --noEmit + vite build) passes clean
+after the edits.
+
+## Non-goals
+
+- The audit does not restart the daemon or vite; those would kill the
+  worker running the audit. Environment drift is classified, not
+  fixed, at runtime.
+- The audit does not synthesize workers or tasks. It reuses the first
+  worker returned by `/api/list`, which is enough to exercise the
+  three `WorkerDetail` variants.
+- The lucide `brokenLucide` probe only flags SVGs with zero children
+  today. Tree-shaken icon paths still render with their path elements
+  intact, so the probe is future-proofing more than a current-state
+  check.
